name	desc	weight	object
"Fox Suit"	"Profoundly light despite its size and supremely cuddly nature, this highly elastic vulpine fursuit might have cost someone a pretty penny, at least in the days before it was possible to become a fox. Now though, the thing is little more than an idle curiosity of a bygone age, with little obvious use beyond serving as insulation during a cold evening, or perhaps blocking the odd punch from a weaker feral. Despite this, it's hard not to admire the silky texture of orange fur covering much of its surface, or the subtle opalescent quality of the creamy white splotch running down its core and inner thighs. Much less the dense layer of snuggly softness coating it, along with the oddly realistic quality of the faux digitigrade legs, plush bubble butt, and the cute girly bend of its arms. Hidden beneath a thick layer of downy smooth fur along its groin though, is a convenient little pink latex slit permitting ease of access to your more *ahem* [italic type]sensitive areas[roman type] when the need arises."	2	Fox Suit

