"Vulpine Mask"	"Undeniably cute and phenomenally fluffy, your foxy mask would look just as fitting at home, at any con, or worn by some high-end corporate mascot. This fetching little costume piece seems to be modeled after the common red fox, as much of its surface is covered in reddish-orange faux-fur with an adorable streak of nacre white running down this neck. Its eyes though have striking magenta irises that seem to the movement of its observers, how though, you're not quite certain. As the now large lifeless mask appears to lack any internal mechanism to facilitate such fanciful effects, regardless, the exotic hue is rather fetching in its own right. Its ears meanwhile walk a thin line between the more classical canine shape and a broad fennec's unusual structure with noticeable tufts of black fur on their tips. Internally though, its black balaclava is covered in streaks of rich amethyst purple likely left but its former inhabitants. While safe to handle for the moment, you're under no illusion that putting this on won't transform you on the spot."	4	Vulpine Mask

