to say EventConditions_Fur_Finder:
	if Cunt Count of Player >= 1 and "Sterile" is not listed in feats of Player:
		now CurrentWalkinEvent_ConditionsMet is true;

Fur Finder is a situation.
ResolveFunction of Fur Finder is "[ResolveEvent Fur_Finder]".
Sarea of Fur Finder is "Nowhere".

to say ResolveEvent Fur_Finder:
	say "     Ambling along the vine-choked market street, your eyes are drawn to a trio of massive, car-length claw marks scoring the mossy sidewalk and several smashed storefronts. Though you can't be certain of their origins, their size, alongside their odd dispersion reminds you of the wyverns populating the skies. Perturbed and maybe just a hair nervous, you quickly scan the firmament for the culprit, yet whatever creature made these vast rents in foliage and cement seems to have departed. For how long you can't be sure, nor can you ascertain what it was searching for, or perhaps, chasing after through this strange stretch of green. You muse, catching sight of several smaller still-weeping gashes in the nearby plants growing over a partially collapsed wooden doorway framed by moss-coated red brick. To your eyes, the cuts are frantic and wild as if whoever made hurriedly trying to clear a path, to little avail. You note, strolling further down the fracturing sidewalk, observing several more failed attempts where rotting root-choked boards have been haphazardly snapped, or vine-bound doors have been part way ripped off their hinges.";
	say "     Alongside a number of bent tree limbs creeping out of the walls of the adjacent building that seem to have been growing over the entrance of a large alleyway. Cracked at a near ninety degree angle, they appear to be utterly stripped of leaves, and worn slightly smooth, you can almost picture the unlucky soul who made these marks clinging to them as they were born aloft by their assailant. Or perhaps, some hopeful side of you ruminates, they were able to slip into the overgrowth filling the alleyway. Regardless, the curious survivor in you can't help but wonder if there is anything of value to be had in this newly unearthed backstreet. Who knows, you might even find a way inside one of these shops? True, you doubt the former markets or high rise boutiques had much in the way of useful supplies before the outbreak, but even the tiniest bit of non-perishable food, or salvage can have its use, if not to you, then someone else. You shrug, carefully ducking beneath them and quietly crawling between the gaps. Once through, you let out a dejected sigh as you're greeted by the sight of the ruined root and vine clogged side streets.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Everywhere you look, the buildings are beginning to buckle and belly out as opportunistic plants pour through the cracks in the mortar. New growth steadily creeps through the area, filling it with a near solid bulwark of verdant plant matter. While the few doorways you can see peeking through this green hell have already collapsed in on themselves, and in places some of the visible wood appears to have come alive as virgin shoots and velvety crimson blooms gently blow on the slight breeze wafting through the area. Casting your gaze further towards this soon-to-be green tide filling the area, you spy a glint of metal simmering in the low shadows of the alleyways. Intrigued, and in no mood to leave empty handed, you carefully paw up to it and brush aside some of the smaller runners to reveal the latch of an overturned box truck buried underneath. Nearly fused to the encroaching emerald hills, the stricken vehicle is covered with dirt, rust, and supple green runners burrowing into the metal with wild abandon.";
	say "     Rightly curious, you don't see any harm in trying the seemingly unsecured handle, you give the thing a good tug and let out an amused whistle as it turns with a plaintive metallic crack before surging up [']upwards['] revealing a shadowy void behind it. Yet, as your eyes adjust to the gloom, you note the truck seems to be empty save for a single white cardboard box, roughly the size of a large microwave flipped over near the rear of the vehicle resting atop a pile of dark loamy soil. Doing a quick double check to make sure you're not about to walk into the maw of some clever monster, or fall into an exotic trap, you confidently stride over to the parcel and hastily rip it open without a second thought. Though as the cardboard falls away you can't help, but chuckle at the sight of its fuzzy contents. A fursuit? You chuff, pulling out a partial body suit covered in bright reddish-orange faux-fox fur with a soft cream streak of white running down its core, groin, and inner thighs.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Oddly, the suit seems to be missing its head, hands, feet, and tail. However, as you fluff it out to better take in its size, a note falls out of the box, and lands on the floor with a quiet swish. Picking it up, you quickly skim through the contents to find that there seems to have been a mix up at the delivery center, and the pieces were sent to different parts of the city and are awaiting pick up. Apparently, all the owner, or whoever was going to collect it on their behalf had to do was present this bill, and the shipping company would have handed it, no questions asked. Just your luck, you can't believe you're finding something like this in the middle of a furry apocalypse, it's just too rich. You titter as you contemplate throwing it away, after all if you wanted to become a [italic type]big fluffy snuggle wuggly fox[roman type], er fox you correct yourself while shaking your head, there are plenty cute of vixens and big sexy tods that could make you one for real.";
	say "     Still, as you absentmindedly run your fingers through the rich silky fur and dense soft huggable padding, a part of you wonders if you should hang on to it. The padding alone could probably protect you from the odd punch or kick, and on the rare cold night the extra floof could come in handy. Perhaps, you could even try it on, as you doubt that it's infectious as, at least going by the dates on the shipping bill, the thing seems to have been in transit well before the outbreak so it should be safe. Even it if not, there are worse things to end as than a [italic type]big bubbly cuddly fox[roman type], you mean fox you grumble as you eye up the partial suit warily looking for any abnormalities, hidden traps, or devious mechanisms worked into the [italic type]warm cushy fur[roman type]. Yet no matter how hard you look, you can't find anything off about the fabric, do you risk putting it on, save it for later, or leave this place?";
	LineBreak;
	say "     [bold type]What would you like to do[roman type]?";
	LineBreak;
	let down_to_fox_Choices be a list of text;
	add "Put it on?" to down_to_fox_Choices;
	add "Keep it?" to down_to_fox_Choices;
	add "Leave it?" to down_to_fox_Choices;
	let down_to_fox_Choice be what the player chooses from down_to_fox_Choices;
	if down_to_fox_Choice is:
		-- "Put it on?":
			say "     Oh what the heck, there are worse things to end up as than an [italic type]adorable snuggly vulpine[roman type], besides you have no idea if this thing will even fit you till you try it on. You muse, fumbling around the suit soft creamy tummy fur and velvety rear pelt for the zipper, though it takes you a moment as the tiny thing is hidden under a generous layer of puffy hair, you find the zipper tucked beneath the collar then carefully unzip it and step inside, one [italic type]paw[roman type], you mean foot at a time. Remarkably the suit, though somewhat tight, seems to accommodate you quite nicely. ";
			if Player is impreg_now:
				say "Despite your condition, a part of you finds the sensation of thick cuddly padding stretching around your cute baby bump rather soothing in its own right. You preen, pulling the main body over yours as you zip yourself. You have to admit, the added cushion really brings out your curves and growing swell of lovely tumby, perhaps it was made for a big sexy breeder like yourself.";
				say "     You ruminate, imagining some lucky mother parading this before her adoring mate while you run your mitts though the silky fur, delighting at the dense fabric, gently hugging and supporting your well-loved middle like a down comforter. Though as your hands drift further south alone the creams contours of your fur-wrapped tum, your infatuation only grows as your curious digits brush a slit neatly placed just above your own. Slipping some fingers between the tight folds, you can't resist snicker as your digits brush a snug band of glossy latex worked into its fuzzy borders. Unnaturally warm to the touch, you could almost mistake it for real flesh, perhaps with a little lube though you could complete the illusion. Your lewd mind hums, as you withdraw fingers and turn your attention to the suit's arms.";
			else:
				say "As your legs easily slip into the fetching legging with only the tiniest bit of stretching. You then pull the main body over yours and zip yourself up, while noting the careful dispersion of padding and fine cut of the legs have been made to the effect a faux digitigrade stance. Much to the makers credit, this fanciful addition doesn't encumber you in the slightly, well at least no more than any other suit would as the dense cuddly matter is still a touch hard to move it. You shrug, turning your attention to the suit's arms."; [merge here]
			say "     Albeit simple in design, the seams impart a somewhat feminine look to your limbs, by no means displeasing to you though as the lovely curves pair well with the suit's cushy bubble butt and ample hips. You preen internally, turning around and giving your, er, you pause to once more shake your head, the suit's ass a gentle squeeze. Nice, it's like having your own portable cushion, you purr as your palms sink into the dense pillowy fabric reveling at the way the stuffing hugs your fingers and fur caresses your [skinname of Player] skin. Your tainted mind still wonders what it would be like to put this thing through its paces with some of the big sexy foxes roaming the city, or perhaps cuddling with it on some nice soft bed. You smirk, letting your elated digits roam the cute cuddly curves of your latest find as you exalt in a tender layer of verdant softness swaddling you. Keeping it clean though will surely be a chore, but that's a problem for future you, and hey what's that person ever done for you, you titter as you gather your things and head back to the Overgrown Street.";
			ItemGain Fox Suit by 1;
			Now Fur Finder is resolved;
		-- "Keep it?":
			say "     Not wanting to damage, or sully this adorable, and potentially valuable little trinket by exposing it to the muck and depraved attention of the various ferals wandering about on your inevitable return to the bunker. You carefully refold the incomplete suit into a neat square, mindful not to damage the stitch work, or impart any unnecessary creases into the fabric, before tucking the oddly-light costume away for later. Who knows, perhaps you might one day be able to reunite this thing with its owner, whoever they are. Or, you could even resell it, despite its incomplete state, there are a number of suspiciously wealthy furries out there willing to pay a decent price for something like this. If nothing else, the fetching thing could serve as a cute set of pajamas, or a fine gift to a friend. Regardless, you doubt there's anything more to find in this place, well not unless you want to start tunneling through the wall of the various buildings, yet given the state of the area. You'd most likely cause the distressed buildings to collapse long before you find anything of value. You shrug, making your way back to the Overgrown street.";
			ItemGain Fox Suit by 1;
			now Fur Finder is resolved;
		-- "Leave it?":
			say "     Unable to shake a budding sense of wariness building in your breast as you banefully eye up this seemingly innocent costume, you decide to err on the side of caution, and fold this suit back up, then slip its back into its box. Though you can't see anything out of the ordinary about it now, your time in the city has taught you that this may not remain the case for long. Who knows this could be some elaborate ruse by a particularly wily feral, infected person, or extra planar creature to lure you into if not the dawning suit, then transporting it somewhere a more gullible person will. Either way, best play it safe lest you tempt fate, well more than you usually do. You snicker, drifting back to the Overgrown Street and away from whatever fresh spore of madness you might have stumbled upon.";
			now Fur Finder is resolved;
			Increase XP of Player by 5;



Table of GameEventIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Flying Fuxis	"Flying Fuxis"

Table of WalkInEvents (continued)
Priority	Name	EventObject	EventConditions	EventRoom	LastEncounterTurn	CoolDownTurns	EncounterPercentage
1	"Flying Fuxis"	Flying Fuxis	"[EventConditions_Flying_Fuxis]"	Northern Docks	2500	2	100

to say EventConditions_Flying_Fuxis:
	if HP of Mistress Snuggle is 4 and Cunt Count of Player >= 1:
		now CurrentWalkinEvent_ConditionsMet is true;

Flying Fuxis is a situation.
ResolveFunction of Flying Fuxis is "[ResolveEvent Flying_Fuxis]".
Sarea of Flying Fuxis is "Nowhere".

to say ResolveEvent Flying_Fuxis:
	say "     Striding past the usual gaggle of exotic streetwalkers hocking themselves on the districts northern most reaches, you stop for a moment to admire, or perhaps even considered purchasing the services of some of the more interesting mutants prowling the area. As their time spent in company of countless post-human partners, and maybe even some measure of personal experimentation has left many of the local whores sporting some rather... unique forms. You opine, shuffling past a gaggle of buxom goopy pink cat girls prowling near the water's edge. Naked as they day they were born, the kitty gels stand taller than most basketball players, towering head-and-shoulders above the crowd. They seem to take a great deal of pride in their morphic nature as they shift and flex their hands into all manner of lewd toys meant to entice the passersbys. Others of a more milky persuasion gleefully knead their ponderous rows of oh-so-palmable breasts, offering any brave soul the chance to try a sample of strawberry cream. Though a curious side briefly toys with the notion of trying a bit yourself, but you think better of it, you have things to take care of first, you note picking your way through the crowd of potential johns.";
	say "     You duck into one of the many alleyways dotting the area to avoid notice. Once you're sure you are alone, you pull out the crumpled note with Flying Fuxi's address before setting off into the ratty back streets. Already a maze-like mess before the outbreak, the area has grown all the more unnavigable by the occasional collapsed building blocking some of the more direct routes and soaring piles of trash left behind by the area's current and former residents. You grumble, coming across a partially collapsed brick warehouse blocking yet another pathway in. Packed shoulder-high with mounds of shattered aggregate and rotting unidentifiable piles of brown matter, the area reeks of rot, and fouling oil that seems to clings to the back of your throat with every breath. Briefly, you consider simply mantling the rubble then picking your way through, but think better of it as the light shifts, and your eyes catch sight of the shimmering outlines of pale spider webs swaying in the salty breeze. Were you a less traveled sort, you might have paid them little mind, and simply cut your way though, but your time in the city as taught you better, as your recognize the telltale signs of the local Driders.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Instead, you dejectedly shake your head then plod on past looking for yet an alternative path, the going is slow though as you encounter more such 'traps' dotting the meandering pathways, alongside scrapes of tattered cum soaked clothing. Bypassing each takes time, and while you entertain the notion of simply barreling your way through their webs. You have no quarrel with these ferals, at least, not for the moment, nor any notion of how many are scurrying about. You ruminate, trudging down a trash strewn corridor on your less-then-scenic route to the borders of the district. Here, the webs seem to give way as the area opens up towards the borders of the Red Light District while you once more pull out the shipping bill, then count off the few visible addresses as you reorient yourself, then push on for several more blocks. Till at least, you find yourself along a tightly packed row of plain two story brutalist cement buildings, separated by only a few inches of litter packed space between, strolling down this banal lane of structures, idly reading off the names and address of each.";
	say "     Though most are simply called some variation of Warehouse 1-A, 2-B, and 9-S, a few stick out like the bright yellow and black sheet metal sign with the words South Pacific Kinetic Solutions craved into it with quick messy welding cuts, the oddly italicized crimson and black banner of North-Side Storage, or the gaudy Chibi construction worker mascot of Toha Heavy Industries. Your eyes soon light up as you catch sight of cartoonish Flying Fox sailing through a clear blue backdrop with an old timey brown mailman's satchel wrapped around it torse with the words 'Flying Fuxi's' written in a fanciful, if dated cursive scrawl. Jackpot! You exclaim, in raw jubilation as the building seems not only intact, but unguarded, though a modest metal security door still bars your entrance. While by no means impressive, the reinforced apparatus seems to have kept the ferals out for the moment, looking all the closer at the rusted steel bolts driven into the cement though. You realize the thing could be easily shorn from the with the right tools, some muscle, and a little time.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Of course, there might be a loading dock or bay out back you could try to, though that would likely mean confronting the Driders on their own turf. While by no means the most dangerous creatures, if the other streets are any indication, these ferals have had more than enough time to prepare their webs. So any intrusion will more than likely lead to a fight, one you will most assuredly be on the back foot on. Then again, the RLD isn't too far off, if worst comes to worst, it shouldn't be hard to flee the locals.";
	LineBreak;
	say "     [italic type]With all this in mind, what do you want to do?[roman type]";
	let Open_says_me_Choices be a list of text;
	add "Try the rear." to Open_says_me_Choices;
	if Crowbar is wielded or Claw Hammer is wielded:
		add "Pry open the door." to Open_says_me_Choices;
	let Open_says_me_Choice be what the player chooses from Open_says_me_Choices;
	if Open_says_me_Choice is:
		-- "Try the rear.":
			say "      Deciding to try your luck out back, you hurriedly skirt around the edges of the block and begin searching for some side street, or connected alleyway leading to Fuxi's rear. Sure enough, not more than several buildings down, you spy a cracked utility road winding behind the largely abandoned structures, pitted with potholes, broken glass, and yellowed, sun-faded cigarette butts ground into the greyish-brown dirt. Idly sniffing the air, the faint hints of fouling petrol and stale bodily fluids nip once more at your senses, beneath it all though you can smell some coiling hints of cheap oaky cologne wafting about the area. Further in, the area is clogged with the same silky grey stands of webbing you saw dotting the edges of the Northern Docks. Though many are tattered, or coated in a thick black and grey coat of building dust, others yet gleam with pale white glow as if their surfaces were bathed in a shimmering stream of prismatic pearls. Undeterred, and more than confident you can handle a Drider, even on its own turf, you boldly stride forth into the gloom, batting aside any errant webs that cross your path.";
			say "     Your progress is slow though as though stands resist you attempts to peel them back, yet through sheer bullheadedness still manage to cleave a path through the dilapidated street. All the while counting down the number of buildings you pass to keep yourself oriented with your quarry. Fixated as you are on clearing the path ahead, you hardly notice something shifting in the shadows shifting over head as a dark ash gray and lurid salubrious black shape creeps over head with deliberate slowness while the light beings to dance across the sleek back curves of this arachnid feral as it leaps down, its legs splayed outward as if to pin you. ";
			if Driver Carbine is wielded:
				say "Idiot, you chuff under your breath, lips curling into a menacing smirk, as quickly heft your carbine, and fire several volleys into the foolish feral. Though some go wide, many more hit the bastard square in its bestial core while it howls in unnatrual agony as the force of the impact sends it creaning to the side as it slams into a nearby wall with pitiable thud. Stunned and gasping for breath, the horrid hybrid struggles to rise, yets it lower-half seems deaden from the fall and simply twitches in a pained palsy-like state as the monstrous thing's humanoid half tries in vain to heft itself off the ground. In no mood to toy with them though, you quickly charge forward, and club them with the butt of your gun, then watch as it collapses with a satisfying thud.";
				say "[Fuxi's_rear]";
			else if Mad Gun is wielded:
				say "Almost chuckling at the foolishness of this vile arachnid, you hurriedly level your Mad gun at the insipid nat's core, and fire several rough volleys as it descends. Bereft any visible effects, the look of confusion on the pale-skinned creep is one you'll savor for days as its body begins wildly convulsing, then goes deathly still. As at its once haughty mug impacts the trash strewn ground with a meaty thump, sending filth and garbage spraying in all directions. Dumbass, you chuff, shouldering your heavy rifle.";
				say "[Fuxi's_rear]";
			else:
				say "Sneering and mentally prepared for such a cowardly attack, you hurl yourself to the side, though the hooked edges of its legs still manage to clip the side of your face as it with a chittering swish, before advancing up on you.";
				PlayerWounded 15;
				Challenge "Spidertaur Male";
				if fightoutcome >= 10 and fightoutcome <= 19:
					say "     Cowed by your ferocious assault, the horrid mongrel howls in defeats as sweat laced with the dust and rot pours down its all-too-human face as suddenly leaps on the sides of nearby building, then skitters off into it's webby lair. Of no mind to chase it down, much less pick your way though the tangled mess of threads dotting the area, you let the thing go, content in the knowledge that at least for the moment, it won't bother you any further. Still, it best not to rest on your laurels when other such cretins could be lurking in the rafters.";
					say "[Fuxi's_rear]";
				else if fightoutcome >= 20 and fightoutcome <= 29:
					say "     [italic type]Sometime later[roman type], you awaken near the edge of the northern docks, alive but rattled, and covered in what you dearly hope is [bold type]just[roman type] webbing. You slowly pick yourself up off the ground, and dust off what you can before sighing in defeat, resigning yourself to never return to this stupid place, no damn suit is worth this hassle!";
					now Flying Fuxis is resolved;
				else if fightoutcome >= 30:
					say "     Sensing your impending defeat, you hurriedly dart back through the utility street with the drider hot on your tail, yet for all its horrid eight-legged speed, you still manage to avoid its grasp as you thoughtlessly barrel towards the red light district. Nearing the border though, the thing soon stops in its tracks with an odd dumbfounded look on its oddly human visage as it seems to lose interest in and begins shuffling off to its foul warren. In no mood to question the feral's behavior, you merely shrug and resolve to never bother the beast, as no fanciful trinket is worth this headache!";
					now Flying Fuxis is resolved;
					move Player to Entrance to the Red Light District;
		-- "Pry open the door.":
			say "     Knew this thing would come in handy, you muse while a self satisfied smirk tugs at the edges of your [headname of Player] lips, as you brandish preferred clawed tool and proceed to pry away the crumbling bolts with a few well placed tugs. Though noisy, the area seems clear for the moment, allowing you free reign to be as wild and brutish as you need to rip the gate off its moorings. Sure enough, after several minutes of rough pulling and a couple expertly placed smacks, the metal door begins to sag to one side as you shear each bolt loose, till with one frightful metallic knell, the door slips free, and clangs against the ground. Behind it, you spy a simple green painted wood door decorated with a clear hex pattern window, alongside a graceful bronze handle. On a lark, you give the thing a gentle tug, only for it to rattle in your grasp. Locked, oh well, you shrug, as you quickly smash out the glass with butt of your tool, then reach inside, and fumble around for the interior handle. Though it takes a few tries, the door soon swings open with a well oiled swish as you hurriedly slip past, then shut the thing behind you.";
			say "[Fox_hole]";

To say Fox_hole:
	say "     Once inside, you do a quick sweep of the lobby, though dark, the place appears rather spartan as only a few blue plastic chairs arrayed near the entrance. A smattering of posters depicting the same flying fox mascot decorating much of the clean white walls. Plain black slip resistant plastic mats have been thrown over the white linoleum floor while a red analog ticket dispenser parked next to a plexiglass wall situated in front of the tellers stand sits towards the rear. Nestled behind it, is a sturdy looking metal mesh door painted a bland malilla. Beside the booth, you spy a second solid green metal door with a thin one way viewing window with a sign beneath it emblazoned with the words: 'Staff Only' upon a gleaming copper plate. Intrigued, you paw up to the thing, and give the handle an experimental tug, and are rewarded by an oddly satisfying little metallic *click* as the thing swings open without resistance.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Peering in, you find the area is almost pitch black, though small streaks of ambient light still peter from thin cracks in the walls. Thankfully, the area seems to have been deserted for some time as the omnipresent scents of sex and drying juices appear absent. Beaming at your good fortune, you slip inside and are greeted by stacks of all manner of cardboard boxes piled floor to the ceiling in a vast single story grey cement room, alongside canvas bags of stuffed full of letters and envelopes. Reasoning your quarry is likely still tucked away in one of the boxes, and just a hair curious what other spoils could be waiting for you, you select one of the rows at random, then begin tearing them open with reckless abandon. Though their recipients maybe gone, or turned, there's nothing saying you can't put whatever baubles they constrain to better use.";
	say "     [italic type]Two hours later[roman type], and you've gutted the last box, and have little to show for your efforts. True, you manage to score a few bags of exotic chips and soda, alongside some meds meant for the city hospital. Most of the fare seems to be little more than the odd ugly sweater, or personal effects of little use to your current situation. Still, the savvy scav in you is all too happy to add what you can to your personal hoard, yet the suit's paws and tail elude you nonetheless. Dejected, but undeterred, you begin searching through the packing foam strewn about the area for any boxes you might have missed, as you explore the shadowy room further though, you find an another tucked door labeled: 'Returns and Undeliverables' which seems to lead deeper into the boxy building. Reasoning, you'll have more luck in the second section, you pop on in, then find yourself in a bare grey annex packed full of bright yellow cloth mesh push carts taller than a man's waist, while its walls are lined with brown wooden cubbies. Most seem empty, or full of spam letters, yet one pops out to you as your eyes catch sight of a largely unassuming brown cardboard box covered in mail stamps and bright red seals from several other companies with a large stack of crumpled paper affixed to its side.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Recalling the previous mix up your [italic type]snuggly wuggly[roman type] suit endured before you saved it, you surmise this must be what you're looking for. Though as a curious side of you can't help but want to take a look at the extra paper work first, there could be some clues as to the whereabouts of your prize's head. You muse, thumbing through the sheet of paper, most are rather boilerplate, like logs, receipts, and even a few import labels, sorting through them with a clinical eye, you spy some (poorly) handwritten letters mixed in. Skimming them over, you realize they belong to the suits owner, and contain their inquiries about the status of '[italic type]Snuggle[roman type]'. At first, the initial missives seem rather banal, but as the volumes drone on through, their tone gets more frantic, and bordering on unhinged as they plead with the company to quote: [']find hir[']. They even go so far as to include some rather risque picture of a shapely nude reddish-orange fox herm along with a few female ones dressed in skimpy bondage gear. As the series of letters ramble on, the writer begins peppering in strange details about their characters, and adventures explore various popular franchises, looting all manner of treasures, and tales of their many children as if this would somehow aid in their discovery.";
	say "     Almost groaning, you feel your eyes start to glaze over at their laundry list of powers, which range from the overtly magic, to the eclectic ability to absorb or devour both people and animals and assimilate their traits into themselves. None of which seems to have moved the clerks assigned to this case, as the poor damned souls meant to handle such inquiries all seem to have sent the same generic response, procure the same slip you found earlier and they'll release the parcel. From the haughty replies, this went over about as well as you expected, for there all the various missives devolve into childish diatribes, and Karen-like demands that ultimately went nowhere. Shrugging, you continue flicking through the remaining notes till you run across another from a different shipping company called: Fed-Up Express. Detailing their own troubles with this client alongside a confirmation that the head is being kept at one of their off-sight storage lockers. Going by the address, the place doesn't seem all that far from the Abbey proper. Grinning at your good fortune, you debate ripping the package open, but think better of, best pack this thing somewhere with a bit more light, you muse, tucking the box under your arm, and head back the way you came towards the way you came.";
	now Flying Fuxis is resolved;
	ItemGain Cardboard Box by 1;
	ItemGain Soda by 2;
	ItemGain chips by 2;
	ItemGain Medkit by 2;
	now HP of Mistress Snuggle is 5;

To say Fuxi's_rear:
	say "     With the brute dealt with, you continue on your down the web clogged street, eyes darting between the remaining glittering threads and shadows as you close in on, what you assume to be the building's simple grey concrete loading dock protruding out into the road. Intrigued, but still reasonably cautious, you do a quick double take to make sure no more eight-legged freaks are waiting in the wings before striding over to the thing's metal rolling shutters. Unlike the front, these seem to be secured with little more than a common silver combination lock with a plain black dial. Reasoning the thing is no tougher than a basic bike lock, you scout around the area for anything you could use to bash, or pry the flimsy looking construct apart. Moments later, you find several pieces of what you surmise was a steel school chair's legs poking out the moldering heaps of refuse polluting the area. Despite their willowy nature, you reason they should be enough for the task at hand, and scoop them up, the amble back over the lock. Threading them through the its shackle, you apply a quick bit of leverage on the metal till the thing cracks with a satisfying crunch as the cheap pot iron snaps apart.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Pulling the remains loose, you dexterously prop up the shutters enough for you to slip underneath then roll under, and quietly close the thing behind you. Inside, you're met with a thick gloomy pall as the building seems to lack much in the way of windows, as a few thin bands of light peeking through the roll-up doors illuminate the area. Yet as your eyes adjust, you're greeted by stacks of all manner of cardboard boxes piled floor to the ceiling in a vast single story grey cement room, along canvas bags of letters and envelopes. Reasoning your quarry is likely still tucked away in one of the box, and just hair curious what other spoils could wait you, you select one of the rows at random, then begin tearing them open with reckless abandon for though their recipients maybe gone, there's nothing you can't put whatever baubles they constrain to better use.";
	say "     [italic type]Two hours later[roman type], and you've gutted the last box, and have little to show for your efforts. True, you manage to score a few bags of exotic chips and soda, alongside some meds meant for the city hospital. Most of the fare seems to be little more than the odd ugly sweater, or personal effects of little use to your current situation. Still, the savvy scav in you is all too happy to add what you can to your personal hoard, yet the suit's paws and tail elude you nonetheless. Dejected, but undeterred, you begin searching through the packing foam strewn about the area for any boxes you might have missed, as you explore the shadowy room further though, you find an another tucked door labeled: 'Returns and Undeliverables' which seems to lead deeper into the boxy building. Reasoning, you'll have more luck in the second section, you pop on in, then find yourself in a bare grey annex packed full of bright yellow cloth mesh push carts taller than a man's waist, while its walls are lined with brown wooden cubbies. Most seem empty, or full of spam letters, yet one pops out to you as your eyes catch sight of a largely unassuming brown cardboard box covered in mail stamps and bright red seals from several other companies with a large stack of crumpled paper affixed to its side.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Recalling the previous mix up your [italic type]snuggly wuggly[roman type] suit endured before you saved it, you surmise this must be what you're looking for. Though as a curious side of you can't help but want to take a look at the extra paper work first, there could be some clues as to the whereabouts of your prize's head. You muse, thumbing through the sheet of paper, most are rather boilerplate, like logs, receipts, and even a few import labels, sorting through them with a clinical eye, you spy some (poorly) handwritten letters mixed in. Skimming them over, you realize they belong to the suits owner, and contain their inquiries about the status of '[italic type]Snuggle[roman type]'. At first, the initial missives seem rather banal, but as the volumes drone on through, their tone gets more frantic, and bordering on unhinged as they plead with the company to quote: [']find hir[']. They even go so far as to include some rather risque picture of a shapely nude reddish-orange fox herm along with a few female ones dressed in skimpy bondage gear. As the series of letters ramble on, the writer begins peppering in strange details about their characters, and adventures explore various popular franchises, looting all manner of treasures, and tales of their many children as if this would somehow aid their discovery.";
	say "     Almost groaning, you feel your eyes start to glaze over at their laundry list of powers, which range from the overtly magic, to the eclectic ability to absorb or devour both people and animals and assimilate their traits into themselves. None of which seems to have moved the clerks assigned to this case, as the poor damned souls meant to handle such inquiries all seem to have sent the same generic response, procure the same slip you found earlier and they'll release the parcel. From the haughty replies, this went over about as well as you expected, for there all the various missives devolve into childish diatribes, and Karen-like demands that ultimately went nowhere. Shrugging, you continue flicking through the remaining notes till you run across another from a different shipping company called: Fed-Up Express. Detailing their own troubles with this client alongside a confirmation that the head is being kept at one of their off-sight storage lockers. Going by the address, the place doesn't seem all that far from the Abbey proper. Grinning at your good fortune, you debate ripping the package open, but think better of, best pack this thing somewhere with a bit more light, you muse, tucking the box under your arm, and head back the way you came towards the way you came.";
	now Flying Fuxis is resolved;
	ItemGain Cardboard Box by 1;
	ItemGain Soda by 2;
	ItemGain chips by 2;
	ItemGain Medkit by 2;
	now HP of Mistress Snuggle is 5;




Table of GameEventIDs (continued)
Object	Name
Da Final Fox Down	"Da Final Fox Down"

Table of WalkInEvents (continued)
Priority	Name	EventObject	EventConditions	EventRoom	LastEncounterTurn	CoolDownTurns	EncounterPercentage
2	"Da Final Fox Down"	Da Final Fox Down	"[EventConditions_Da_Final_Fox_Down]"	Northwest 7th Street	2500	2	100

to say EventConditions_Da_Final_Fox_Down:
	if HP of Mistress Snuggle is 7 and Foxy Paws is equipped and Cute Tail is equipped and Fox Suit is equipped and Cunt Count of Player >= 1 and "Sterile" is not listed in feats of Player:
		now CurrentWalkinEvent_ConditionsMet is true;

Da Final Fox Down is a situation.
ResolveFunction of Da Final Fox Down is "[ResolveEvent DaFinalFoxDown]".
Sarea of Da Final Fox Down is "Nowhere".

to say ResolveEvent DaFinalFoxDown:
	say "      Trekking along the dull, barren side streets leading towards the [']Store Everything['] facility, you flip out your collection of shipping bills one last time to compare the addresses with those on the various drab buildings populating the area. By some strange stroke of fortune, the ferals seem to have ignored much of this place, as most of the buildings, along with their signage, appears to be unsoiled by the usual chaos afflicting the city. Why though, you can't be certain, perhaps, due to a quirk of timing this place was largely occupied when the outbreak began, or maybe, the area was never popular to begin with? Regardless, your search is blessedly quick, as you count off the address numbers in a slow monotonous tone till you find yourself standing outside of a shuddered three story red brick building. Utterly bland and unadorned, you'd never have guessed the place was ever an active store, much less paid it any mind had you not found the directions. You think to yourself, eyeing up the rolling grey metal shutter draped over much of the first floor, facing the street.";
	say "     Above it, a thin gun metal black fireescape with a dilapidated foldout ladder snakes its way beneath several sets of recessed windows. Long since corroded beyond repair, the paint visibly bubbles in places, and rusty spikes of crystalline oxidized metal pours out from its hinges like the rotten teeth of some long dead creature protrude from it at odd angles. The few remaining bolts hanging from the cracked clay seem to sway and creak with the slightest breeze, and a part of you doubts the thing could ever be fixed, much less support the weight of even the tiniest infected. Casting your gaze towards the dark arsenic green windows, you note the blinds have been drawn closed for quite some time as the white curtains have been bleached on off-yellow boney white by the sun. Tucked about their corners, are the remains of dead flies and greyish-brown pillars of dust piled two fingers high. Strangely, the sight is oddly... comforting in its own way, as you doubt anyone has disturbed this place since the outbreak, meaning much of the spoils (if there are any) would be untouched. Perhaps, you could even use the place as a bolt hole one day, or shelter in the event the bunker were compromised. You hum, a light smirk tugging on the edges of your [FaceName of Player] lips, as you stride over to rolling metal curtain barring entrance to the bodega, lean down, then give the thing an experimental tug.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     To your amazement, it easily glides upwards on well-oiled hinges, revealing a simple glass door framed with flimsy looking metal, painted a fading emerald green, with a rather worn looking handle on the left side of the building. Its waning paint worn glassy smooth, and nearly polished off in places by the touch of countless hands, or the uncaring bite of the elements. To its right, is a large scratched up, weather-beaten plastic window, pitted with keymarks, dents left by bits of gravel flung from the street, and riddled with cloudy spots of interminable origin obscuring much of the store proper. Squinting, you can barely see anything behind its milky white surface, beyond the vague outlines of empty shelves. Shrugging in mild disappointment at the lack of obvious loot, you try the door, only to find it locked, as the aperture roughly rattles on its hinges. No matter, this place seems well and truly empty of life, nanite touched or otherwise, so you opt to smash your way in, rather than dither about looking for a more covert means of entry. You ruminate, swiftly surveying the area for something you could use to break the glass, not like anyone is gonna call the cops on you aways.";
	say "     Peering through the gutters, you find a few fist sized black rocks of indeterminate provenance wedged in a nearby stormdrain's grate, popping them out. You step back, then hurl one at the door with reckless abandon as a loud, satisfying crack resounds through the area while the glass explores in a shower of sparking silicone. Clasping a second stone in hand, you knock out any dangerous looking shards that would bar your path, or threaten your precious suit, then slip through. Inside, you're assailed by the lingering scents of sage, clover, stale tobacco, and the barest hints of rotting plant matter pooling around the entrance as a light breeze nips at your heels. Despite the lack of proper lighting, your nanite-altered eyes can still make out several rows of plain beige painted shelves placed atop a sticky black-and-white checkerboard pattern linoleum floor. Its well-traveled surface is dotted with a prominent line of scuff marks, and the occasional cigarette burn snaking between the shelves. Long since picked bare by quicker survivors, or mayhaps looted by its owner, little of value remains save for some bottles of off-brand condiments, and blue bleach tablets, neither of which are much use to you in your current situation.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Letting your eyes wander along its western walls, you spot a cordoned off cash register tucked behind a thick slab of what you assume is reinforced glass. Behind which, are empty white shelves that, according to the black italicized labels affixed to them, once held (horribly overpriced) booze, cartons of imported smokes, condoms, and feminine hygiene products. Further back, is a study looking grey metal security door that seems untouched by the normal vandalism plaguing the city. Under other circumstances, you might have toyed with the notion of finding your way into the back of the building. For now though, you content yourself with locating the dropoff locker as you scan the rear of the building. Here, you spot a long row of walk-in fridges, their power long since cut, and largely barren. The few remaining food items have spoiled and congealed into an unsightly mass of multi-hued mold unfit for consumption by even the most nanite hardened creature. Adjacent to them, is a large rectangular orange and blue storage unit locker with the words: Fed-Up Express, emblazoned on its side tucked into the corner. There you are! You cheer, striding over to its side.";
	say "     By some strange miracle, the locker is still powered by either an internal battery, or other unseen source, you note, observing the pale neon-white glow of a tiny monitor affixed to its side peaking through the gloom. Flicking through the menu, you punch in the locker ID, followed by the password, and hit [bold type]ENTER[roman type]. A soft mechanical whirl echoes through the machine as a door pops open, inside is a tightly wrapped brown box, covered in duct tape, stickers, and enough stamps to make a customs agent's eyes glaze over in despair. Plucking it free, you hurriedly tear the thing apart with wild abandon, filling the air with sounds of ripping plastic and shearing cardboard as you peel the dense layers of packaging off. Little-by-little, the thing gives way, till with one satisfying *rip* as you pull your suit's plush [italic type]snuggly[roman type] mask free. Much like the rest of your costume, its generously padded, and decorated in silk reddish-orange faux fur with a cute streak of white running down its lean muzzle and [italic type]cuddly[roman type] neck.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "      Leveling its face with your own, it's hard not to be struck by the eerily life-like nature of its gleaming magenta eyes staring back at you expectantly, or the all too realistic quality of its thin ebony lips and teeth as they glisten in the dim light. Were you the sort given to flights of fancy, you would almost swear they look, wet? You shrug, turning it over in your gloved mitts, while its eyes seem to be tracking you. You muse, idly shifting the mask in your hand watching its pupils shift on the quarter turn, then pop back into place when you right the thing. Rolling your eyes, you merely chalk this to some clever trick on the suitmaker's part, whoever they may be. Meanwhile, its long pointy ears straddle the line between a classical vulpine and a fennec's, you ruminate, as the supple lining of your fluffy suit tightens ever-so-slightly about your back and inner thigh cinches about your joints. Far from uncomfortable, the sudden contractions nevertheless catches you off guard as the not-so-little feelers nesting within your costume burst forth from their hidey holes, and frantically coil down the length of your arms towards the head with a sudden, desperate energy. Annoyance and curiosity flare through in equal measure as they wildly tug upon your arms as if urging you to put the head on here and now.";
	say "     Hissing at their impatience, you chastise the pushy creatures, much as you might be looking forward to completing your transformation. You'll decide when and where you do, not them! Yet your words seem to fall on deaf [']ears['] as they snake their way about your wrists and hands, forcibly digging your fingers into the downy fur of your prize. While their central mass presses down on your core, as if trying to force you to take a kneel. Stop! You bellow, to little avail as the tendrils tighten about your skull, roughly craning your neck downwards as they tug all the more frantically upon your arms. Yet, for all their waning strength, you don't feel any malice from them, only a profound sense of desperation. Despite the intensity of their hold, they make no effort to constrict your airway, or put pressure on your vitals. Some even seem... apologetic as they mournfully massage your hands or back like they were trying to comfort you, yet in spite of the tenderness of their touch, they refuse to release you, while their peers remain intent on forcing you to bend.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Perhaps, some analytical side of you posits, as you lock your knees in place, whatever force is animating them is nearly spent. Even now you can feel their grasp weaken, if only slightly, as several of their now ribbon thin bodies go slack, then fall limply against the dense padding for your prized costume with a light thud. If so, they may not have the luxury for time, and are simply trying to complete your transformation before they wither away. While that doesn't excuse their forwardness, you can't fully blame them for this. Besides, you both want this, even if it's potentially for different reasons you opine, as the sweet memories of their touch and the joy your past changes brought you flood the back of your mind. So why not trust them once more, and accept this change here and now?";
	say "     Then again, you've seen more than your fair share of insidious creatures prowling the city leaving all manner of honeypot traps across the land for the unwary. Moreover, you've felt the tempting call of the nanites whispering in your ear, urging you to do things you might have once considered taboo enough to still have some reservations nipping at the back of your mind. In the end, can you truly trust that these things don't have some ulterior motive, or that your desires aren't being twisted by the horny little robots incessantly scratching at the back of your mind? Though it might mean losing out on the foxy form of your dreams, you could easily overpower these creatures if you just wait but a few moments longer. You muse, as a quartet of tendrils slithering about your skull shiver in primordial terror as if sensing your thoughts.";
	LineBreak;
	say "     [italic type]What would you like to do? Allow the suit to finish changing you, or remove it before it gets a chance to change you further?[roman type]";
	LineBreak;
	say "     [italic type]Author's Note: This choice is permanent, electing to remove the suit will lock your Snuggle Fox into its current shape, and each piece can be equipped to reinfect you. In the future, a toggle may be included into the Sundered Codex to allow you to slightly tweak this version of the Snuggle Fox TF slightly. Further, no content or special scenes will be unlocked for you if you refuse this TF[roman type].";
	let Do_da_do_do_Choices be a list of text;
	add "Let them change you?" to Do_da_do_do_Choices;
	add "Get this thing off of you!" to Do_da_do_do_Choices;
	let Do_da_do_do_Choice be what the player chooses from Do_da_do_do_Choices;
	if Do_da_do_do_Choice is:
		-- "Let them change you?":
			say "[Ihateindentingalot]";
		-- "Get this thing off of you!":
			say "     Oh fuck this! You hiss with a sad shake of your head, digging in your heels and locking yourself in place as you refuse to allow the creature to dictate when and where you change, regardless of the effect it may have on them. At once, alarm races through their tepid sinuous forms as they press what little of their strength remains, trying to bend your body to their will. Though not all, as some of their number attempt to plead with you in their own way as they worriedly stroke your [Bodydesc of Player] form, while faint images of your foxy figure in regal repose flicker across your mental landscape. Quivering at their caress flutters across you, as they encouragingly grope your lovely passage or tender [breast size desc of Player] chest. Playfully slipping their silky bodies along your blushing hood in a soft purposeful rhythm, provoking a needy vulpine yip from your lips as your knees begin to buckle.";
			say "     Unwilling to yield so such artless temptation, you bite down on your lip, letting pain laced with indignation flare through your senses as you force your hands open, allowing the head drop from your grip, it collides with the floor with an oddly wet *smack*. The tendrils coiling about your legs, suddenly surge along the [bodydesc of Player] contours of your extremities towards it with frightening urgency. In their moment of laxity, you swiftly kick the thing aside while you tear off your glove then hurl them in the other direction. Severed from their 'main body', the things begin to bubble then hiss as they boil away in a plume of odorless magenta smoke while they convulse about like a fish on a line at the loss of their fellows. Hardening yourself against the brief motes of sympathy flashing through you, you hurriedly undo the remaining binding of your costume and chuck it along with your tail to another far corner of the room, before kicking off your boots with the same brutish zeal.";
			WaitLineBreak;
			say "     Magenta fumes soon fill the store as the writhing, cracking creatures boil away by the second, though the process is blessedly quick, sharp pains of regret still plague your mind watching their flailing body decay before your eyes. Never once though do they make any attempt at retribution, or flee from you, instead those still capable of movement attempt to crawl back together, yet this too is short lived as their unnatural flesh sloths off their disintegrating forms. Leaving steaks of purple and black matter in their wakes as they inch forward, bodies stretched their limits as they blindly reached for their peers, only to collapse seconds later. While the last remnant of their slippery being crumples away like amethyst ash caught in a breeze, in their place you spy a thin dusting of silvery powder spiraling along the floor where they fell. Unsure what to make of this, you grab a large plastic bottle of ketchup bottle off the shelves, and poke the now still costume segment along with the powder to see if there is any life remaining in either.";
			say "     Despite your rough prodding, nothing stirs, leaving you wondering, if only briefly, what exactly happened to them as you've never seen a feral, let alone any infected item corrode like that. Perhaps these creatures were unstable, or as you surmised before they were on borrowed time, and simply faded away. Regardless of the truth, your suit should clean now, though whether it remains infectious is anyone's guess, you muse as you collect the various pieces off the floor. Still, this powder they left behind could have some value to the right person, perhaps some of the veteran survivors could shed some light on this? Better yet, an opportunistic side of your beams, someone might even be able to do something with it, what through, you can't be certain, but it could be worth keeping around. You preen, picking through the store for something you could use to transport them. Though precious little material remains in the store proper, you're able to repurpose some of the resealable bleach tablet packaging into a few travel bags. Then proceed to brush up as much as you can for later, and seal them up to the best of your abilities. Once sorted, you tuck your spoils away then head back with your meager haul.";
			LineBreak;
			say "     [bold type]Snuggle fox content ends here, thanks for playing and enjoy your loot... you monster.[roman type]";
			now HP of Mistress Snuggle is 98;
			Increase XP of Player by 69;
			now Morale of Mistress Snuggle is 1;
			ItemGain Vulpine Mask by 1;
			[ItemGain Silvery Powder by 3;]
			now Da final Fox Down is resolved;


