			-- "Abandon this fool notion.":
				say "     Mulling it over for a spell, you decide against pursuing the remaining sections of your suit, though it still gulls to turn back on what could be your only chance to cultivate this infection further. The risks far outweigh the gains, and who knows, in time you might find the vulpine body you crave somewhere out there in the wider city. Perhaps, you could even craft your own form the myriad creatures roaming the world. At least with the common strains, you know risks such changes can bring, not to mention, you'll have a modicum of control over the time and nature of your changes, which is far more than you can say for this odd fur suit. As there is no way to know what the long term effects of it could be, or what manner of creature you'll become. You reason, with a light shrug of your shoulder as you go back to your business.";
