					WaitLineBreak;
					say "     Of course, who's to say you might end up with just one, some covetous facet of your mind crows, you could well end up with a vivid array of limbs to go with your shifting body. Smirking at the thought, you can scarcely dream how delightful it would be to parade such fetching ornaments to your chosen mate's. To say nothing of the utility they could offer in your day-to-day life, you opine, strutting over to some quiet section of the local area, and begin rifling through your inventory for the shipping document you set aside when found your precious prize. Minutes later, you find the folded up thing tucked away in the deepest parts of your inventory. Flicking it open, you hurriedly skim through all the legalese and boiler plate dribble to find your quarry's paws and tail have been sent to some obscure shipping company called: '[bold type]Flying Fuxi's[roman type]' down in the [bold type]warehouse district[roman type]. While the head was sent to, you pause to squint at the rough crease in the page: '[italic type]F*d-U* *xp*e**[roman type].'";
					say "     Fuck, now how are you going to find that thing, you growl, unable to read the crumped text or address. Though your mood soon brightens as you realize there is a chance there might be some record at the Fuxi's of where the head was sent. True, a cynical section of your psyche notes, it might be a long shot, but you've probably gone on looser leads than this. If nothing else, you might find other useful sundries and supplies on this latest excursion, you muse, mind alight with possibilities at manners of spoils await you, as you carefully stash away your lead for later. In the meantime, you'd best prepare for the trip, as all manner of unsavory sorts have made their nest down at the docks.";
